---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/nav/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { breadcrumbs, organization } from '../lib/jsonld';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About AIStudio: The AI Product Reference Database"
  description="AIStudio is a reference database for AI products — think GSMArena or RTINGS, but for AI models and apps. Specs, pricing, and benchmarks, every fact sourced and dated."
  jsonld={[breadcrumbs([{ name: 'About' }]), organization()]}
>
  <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'About' }]} />

  <article class="prose-site max-w-2xl pb-8" data-pagefind-body>
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-3xl">About AIStudio</h1>

    <p class="mt-6">
      Phones have GSMArena. PC parts have PCPartPicker. TVs have RTINGS. AI — the fastest-moving,
      most confusingly priced product category in tech — mostly has hype threads and outdated blog
      posts. AIStudio is the missing reference database.
    </p>

    <p>
      We track the models (GPT, Claude, Gemini, Grok, Mistral, DeepSeek) and the apps built on
      them (Cursor, Windsurf, Lovable, Replit, Bolt, v0) the way a spec database should: exact
      context windows, real per-token prices including cache and batch rates, benchmark scores
      with provenance labels, and API model IDs you can paste into code.
    </p>

    <p>
      Two things make it trustworthy. First, <a href="/methodology">the methodology</a>: every
      fact links to an official source with the date we verified it, and automated checks flag
      anything stale. Second, the data is <a href="https://github.com/ParishKhan/aistudio" rel="noopener">open on GitHub</a> —
      errors get fixed in public.
    </p>

    <h2>Start here</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/models">The model database</a> — specs and pricing for every current model</li>
      <li><a href="/comparisons">Comparisons</a> — head-to-head grids with verdicts</li>
      <li><a href="/pricing">The pricing database</a> — every API rate in one table</li>
      <li><a href="/calculators/token-cost">The token cost calculator</a> — price your workload</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
